$ Oracle: Init parameter MAX_COLUMNS
@ max_columns

The → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/init-parameters[init parameter] `max_columns` was introduced in → development/databases/Oracle/Releases-and-versions/23c and specifies 
the maximum number of → development/databases/Oracle/objects/tables/columns[columns] in a → development/databases/Oracle/objects/tables.

The (default) values `standard` allows 1000 columns, with `extended`, a table can have 4096 columns.

